    "own_identity": "+O",
    "unity": "+U",
    "dependence": "-D"
  },
  "classification": "Natural Kind",
  "reasoning": "LivingBeing is rigid because an entity cannot cease to be a living being without ceasing to exist. It supplies its own identity condition (global identification of an individual organism) and implies unity as living organisms are discrete integrated wholes."
}

{
  "properties": {
    "rigidity": "+R",
    "identity": "+I",
    "own_identity": "-O",
    "unity": "-U",
    "dependence": "-D"
  },
  "classification": "Sortal",
  "reasoning": "A GroupOfPeople is typically rigid because once a collection is identified as a group, it remains one. It carries identity (I) based on its members, but does not provide the primary identity condition itself (O), usually inheriting or relying on the identity of the constituents. It is anti-unity (~U) because it is an aggregate or sum of individuals rather than an intrinsic whole with a single organizing principle like a biological organism."
}

{
  "properties": {
    "rigidity": "+R",
    "identity": "+I",
    "own_identity": "+O",
    "unity": "+U",
    "dependence": "-D"
  },
  "classification": "Natural Kind",
  "reasoning": "Fruit is Rigid because if an instance is a fruit, it cannot cease to be a fruit without losing its identity. It carries Identity but does not supply it (it inherits the Identity Condition from its parent category, such as Biological Entity or Plant Part). Fruit instances are Wholes with internal boundaries (+U) and are not foundationally dependent on other external entities to exist (-D)."
}

{
  "properties": {
    "rigidity": "~R",
    "identity": "+I",
    "own_identity": "-O",
    "unity": "~U",
    "dependence": "+D"
  },
  "classification": "Role",
  "reasoning": "Food is classified as a Role (Anti-Rigid) because the property is contingent; an object (e.g., an apple or a piece of meat) can cease being food while remaining the same object. It does not provide its own identity conditions, as it applies to diverse entities (liquids, solids, biological, chemical) that already carry their own identities. It is externally dependent on a consumer or a process of consumption."
}

{
  "properties": {
    "rigidity": "+R",
