  "reasoning": "Vertebrate is a rigid property because an organism cannot cease to be a vertebrate without ceasing to exist (+R). It carries identity conditions (+I) inherited from the higher-level concept 'Animal', but typically does not supply a unique global identity condition of its own (-O). Instances of vertebrates are viewed as discrete organic wholes (+U) and exist independently of other specific entities (-D)."
}

{
