  "classification": "Role",
  "reasoning": "LegalAgent is anti-rigid (~R) because an instance (a person or corporation) can cease to be a legal agent without ceasing to exist. It carries identity (+I) inherited from its base types but does not supply its own unique identity condition (-O). It is externally dependent (+D) because 'agent' status implies a relationship to a legal system or principal. It is non-unifying (-U) because the varied types of entities that can be legal agents do not share a common unity criterion."
}

{
  "properties": {
    "rigidity": "+R",
