  },
  "classification": "Natural Kind",
  "reasoning": "Organization is a rigid property because an instance of an organization cannot cease to be an organization without ceasing to exist. It supplies its own identity conditions (e.g., legal registration or charter) and imposes unity upon its many parts (members, departments). It is externally dependent because it requires the existence of constituent members (agents) to exist."
}

{
