  "reasoning": "RedApple is non-rigid because a red apple can change color (e.g., rot or be painted) without losing its identity as an apple. It carries identity (inheriting it from the 'Apple' sortal) but does not supply its own unique identity condition (+I, -O). It has unity (+U) as it refers to a discrete whole object, and it is independent (-D) as its existence does not require a specific external relationship."
}

{
  "properties": {
    "rigidity": "~R",
    "identity": "+I",
    "own_identity": "-O",
    "unity": "+U",
    "dependence": "-D"
  },
  "classification": "Role",
  "reasoning": "Caterpillar is a Phase because it is anti-rigid (~R); an instance of a butterfly remains the same individual even when it transitions from being a caterpillar to a pupa or adult. It carries identity (+I) inherited from its substance sortal (e.g., Butterfly/Insect) but does not supply its own unique identity condition (-O). Like most biological organisms, it is a whole (+U) and exists independently (-D)."
}
